author: Nexcell Pride
text:
A great song selection ever. :_ハート:
Sadly I was present on Supaachaato Orei Time, due to I didn't think about a schedule changes.
Also was because I was helping to a friend who got her wallet stolen with all documents.

Well, if Rushia-daitenshi is getting jealousy, it doesn't matter... Maybe a next stream I want to confront her yandere face, now that I've mentioned a friend, when Rushia is preferably first for me. 

Definitively I prefer to being stabbed instead of forgiving me... Sorry :_あせり:
Also I'm waiting for all events ended in fact to ask her for her original song "Butterflies in the huge night sky". I Can't conceive which Vtubers like Aqua-san, Matsuri-san and Marine-san got released their original songs and Rushia-daitenshi is biting the dust. That's my thinking.

Maybe "Butterflies in the huge night sky" would be considered as a fan project, but also is a gift for her. Additionally I became from a Good Master, but sadly he got blamed by third persons. :_おこなのです:

I hope everyone will forgive my extended text and what I'm feeling now.

author: 支えた影
text: Japanese sure is a difficult language..  I checked out the archive for the before/after reaction. The timing was sort of bad tbh, she was going off on a tangent about people in chat having a comedy competition of sorts, drinking her tea in exaggerated anger. Maybe try spending less and having a shorter message for requests? On top of that, the singing stream was already pre-planned to have calm wholesome/seiso healing music. Mirai Nikki ED and the second choice were unfortunately not.. quite that. Better luck next time, sorry to see you didn't get the request through you got properly thanked though. Still much better than dropping a red SC with almost no reaction other than a simple arigatou

author: Amai Ta. Yume
text: Thank you Rushia for everything today! You saved me from getting furious again after a hassling morning. I learned to never forget but to forgive and try to think positive thoughts. It's not temporary, but I learned how to managed my emotions now! It's great! Rushia, I may call you the Necromotion on how you gave me back the emotions but also help me control through your singing. It's true! And I want to thank everyone from JP and EN bros as well as translators on making that happen. Thank you! <3

author: Amai Ta. Yume
text: Membership is so close and I have no money. I might have to skip a month, but I don't want to. I hope the compromise plan that I have will work. Wish me the best of luck! I'll always be a fandead in heart and soul!

author: Amai Ta. Yume
text: And with the 'get a job thing' I'm still studying in college and focus first on my studies. so I shouldn't worry about that right now so much.

author: Redan Kenneth Uy
text: @Amai Ta. Yume  Is your allowance stopped in this pandemic?

author: Amai Ta. Yume
text: In terms of commuting yes, but the government scholarship stipend I'm receiving per month is very slow to put on my account so it's a hassle.and might take a while. I should really try to control myself from superchat giving (I gave a lot to a phoenix and joined with a fox). But never the less, I'll just use exclusive now for membership, (Money flies away so quickly :/)
